# wayvnc configuration — installed to ~/.config/wayvnc/config.
#
# The bind address and port are intentionally NOT set here. They are passed on
# the `exec wayvnc <address> <port>` line in ~/.config/sway/config, which is the
# single source of truth. Setting them in both places makes precedence unclear.
#
# Authentication is disabled: wayvnc has no TigerVNC-style legacy VNC password,
# and its TLS/RSA-AES modes are not a clean match for Guacamole's VNC password
# field. Security is provided by:
#   * binding wayvnc to the Docker bridge gateway only (not 0.0.0.0), and
#   * Guacamole login + permissions + optional TOTP as the public boundary.
# See docs/sway-wayvnc.md for the security rationale.

# No `enable_auth`, no `private_key_file`, no `certificate_file`, no
# `rsa_private_key_file` — leaving auth/TLS off.

# Use the host hardware cursor path off; render cursor in software for headless.
# (Left as wayvnc defaults; uncomment if you observe cursor issues.)
# enable_pam=false
